commit 6e3991082cf41d6dcf397adcc288a966091a9569
Author: Matthew <matthewcurtis@khanacademy.org>
Date:   Fri May 16 08:46:51 2025 -0500

    Add registry guard (#2483)

    ## Summary:
    [See this thread](https://khanacademy.slack.com/archives/C08B8MLKPUZ/p1747236599339659?thread_ts=1747179744.422339&cid=C08B8MLKPUZ)

    The root of the problem we're trying to solve here:

    - We rely on a runtime registry of widgets; right now we do this for `perseus` (both regular registry and editor registry), `perseus-core`, and `perseus-score` (`perseus-core` and `perseus-score` are likely to get merged).
    - These registries map a component type to a chunk of logic specific to the widget.
    - If we try to access a widget that's not registered, we just silently fail (maybe we should throw an error though, why are we trying to access widgets that don't exist?)
    - If we forget to call the register function before accessing the registry, we silently fail for all widgets.

